{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f2128fa8-fe58-4e3a-82bf-caa3f07d652b","content":"Here's what I found:\n\n**`my_app/views.py:3`** — `datetime.now()`\nThis is a hard-coded static call that can't be overridden in tests, making it impossible to assert on time-dependent behavior.\n\n### Recommended fix\n\nUse Django's `timezone.now()` (timezone-aware) and inject it so tests can mock it:\n\n```python\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request, *, _now=timezone.now):\n    now = _now()\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\nThis way tests can pass a fake clock:\n\n```python\ndef test_index():\n    fake = datetime(2026, 1, 1, tzinfo=timezone.utc)\n    response = index(request, _now=lambda: fake)\n```\n\nAlternatively, use `unittest.mock.patch(\"django.utils.timezone.now\")` or the [`freezegun`](https://github.com/spulec/freezegun) library.\n\nOnly **1 file** with **1 instance** was found. The project is small — good time to fix the pattern before it spreads.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"703d721f-407f-4014-9f49-c02edf70bc09","outputTokens":277,"requestId":"6800:228DD8:30AE104:35DCB41:69FD505F"},"id":"4c0b1932-5fcc-48e7-8433-06a2ab823f1a","timestamp":"2026-05-08T02:54:31.958Z","parentId":"7043b8f3-1f04-4be3-b844-c07a483062cf"}
